address="Cham",
pages="588--600",
abstract="This paper discusses the role of safety, availability, and dependability of Internet of Things (IoT) data services dedicated to the monitoring and control of objects in a physical world. These services are designed to be available to devices and users on request at any time and at any location. The Internet of Things differs from today's global Internet in a number of ways. For instance, the networks are typically unmanaged, most of IoT services are safety critical, the link layers are optimized for low power usage, and most nodes have to be implementable in a lightweight manner.",
